AssistantMessage(content=[TextBlock(text='I found **two bugs** — both are timing attack vulnerabilities. The code already imports `hmac` and correctly uses `hmac.compare_digest()` for the internal service token comparison (line 103), but then uses plain string equality (`!=` / `==`) for the `os_security_key` comparisons on lines 110 and 145. This inconsistency makes those checks vulnerable to timing-based side-channel attacks.\n\n**Bugs:**\n- **Line 110** (`get_authentication_dependency`): `token != settings.os_security_key` — unsafe plain comparison\n- **Line 145** (`validate_websocket_token`): `token == settings.os_security_key` — unsafe plain comparison\n\nLet me fix both:')], model='claude-sonnet-4-6', parent_tool_use_id=None, error=None)
