AssistantMessage(content=[TextBlock(text='### Bug Summary\n\nBoth bugs were **timing attack vulnerabilities** — subtle but serious security flaws:\n\n| Location | Line | Bug | Fix |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `get_authentication_dependency` | 110 | `token != settings.os_security_key` | `not hmac.compare_digest(token, settings.os_security_key)` |\n| `validate_websocket_token` | 145 | `token == settings.os_security_key` | `hmac.compare_digest(token, settings.os_security_key)` |\n\n**Why this matters:** Plain string comparison (`==` / `!=`) in Python short-circuits as soon as a character mismatch is found, meaning the time taken varies depending on how many characters of the token match the real key. An attacker can exploit this timing difference to guess the secret one character at a time. `hmac.compare_digest()` runs in **constant time** regardless of where/whether a mismatch occurs, eliminating this side-channel.\n\nNotably, the code already used `hmac.compare_digest` correctly for the internal service token (line 103), making this an inconsistency that the fix now resolves uniformly.')], model='claude-sonnet-4-6', parent_tool_use_id=None, error=None)
